<Link id="l00033" /><CodeLine lineNumber="33"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Data Dependence Graph Node</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00034" /><CodeLine lineNumber="34"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// The graph can represent the following types of nodes:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00035" /><CodeLine lineNumber="35"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// 1 Single instruction node containing just one instruction.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00036" /><CodeLine lineNumber="36"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// 2 Multiple instruction node where two or more instructions from</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00037" /><CodeLine lineNumber="37"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    the same basic block are merged into one node.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00038" /><CodeLine lineNumber="38"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// 3 Pi-block node which is a group of other DDG nodes that are part of a</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00039" /><CodeLine lineNumber="39"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    strongly-connected component of the graph.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00040" /><CodeLine lineNumber="40"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    A pi-block node contains more than one single or multiple instruction</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00041" /><CodeLine lineNumber="41"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    nodes. The root node cannot be part of a pi-block.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00042" /><CodeLine lineNumber="42"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// 4 Root node is a special node that connects to all components such that</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00043" /><CodeLine lineNumber="43"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    there is always a path from it to any node in the graph.</span></CodeLine>
